'''''Metal Fighter''''' is a [[Side-scrolling video game|side-scrolling]] [[shooter game]] developed in Taiwan by [[Thin Chen Enterprise|Joy Van]] and published by [[Color Dreams]] and [[Thin Chen Enterprise|Sachen]]. It was later published as '''''Metal Fighter μ''''' (メタルファイター ミュー) in [[Japan]] by Kinema Music in 1991.

==Gameplay==
The player controls a robot, MCS-920, in an attempt to free planet H17 from alien invaders. MCS-920's weapons and speed can be improved by shooting certain enemies and collecting the power-ups they left behind. There is a special power-up that enables flight.

